name: Doga ka Curfew

description: Inez and Yulan leave the cradle of civilization behind and enter uncharted territory. On their journey, they start accumulating some traveling companions--a cute, harmless creature named Mong, a darkly beautiful, insolent Kyrette and a half-elf named Ariel. Sidetracked by Ariel's plight, Inez finds herself drawn to helping the half-elf, getting the entire group into some big trouble.
name: Vol. 2

description: When Mong is captured and imprisoned in a magic cage, Inez and the gang are on the quest to search for the magic key to release him. With two little Big Ears as their guides, Inez and Kyrette make their way to Rever's palace. Black magic is in the air as the group fights to defeat the villianous elf, Rever. But just as victory draws near, another danger looms in the horizon!
name: Vol. 3

description: Lilith places a hypnotic spell on Kyrette and Inez in order to get to Yulan. Yulan's true desires are revealed when he deserts Inez in a time of need. A new player named Neo joins Kyrette on his mission to find the power of the dragon essence. Kyrette's true intentions unfold in the story. Inez falls into a state of confusion and pain after Kaager reveals vital information about her existence. Will Inez be the One to save the kingdom?
name: Vol. 4

description: Ezekiel visits his long time "acquaintance" Lord Minos, a high-level but tarnished elf who only seeks pleasure, fun and youth in the City of Ecstasy. Minos' love for Ezekiel is evident, but apparently Ezekiel has a different agenda...
name: Vol. 5

description: Kyrette and Inez's path crosses once again in the forests of Eloam. Kyrette does not recognize Inez, and when asks her name, Inez tells him she’s Enril, without knowing who that is. The energy of Eloam is lethal for both Yulan and Kyrette, as they fall unconscious with high fever. Meanwhile, Irez gets caught in a labyrinth of memories. Can Yulan or Kyrette recover from their sickness to save her?
name: Vol. 6

description: In a tale of courage, tragedy and betrayal, this glimpse into the distant past of Arcana tells the story of the first Enril and how an ordinary village girl tamed a dragon and gained the ultimate power. What ties, nearly forgotten and buried in the sands of time, does Enril have with our young heroine, Inez?
name: Vol. 7

description: The tale of Enril, a human girl who came to possess the holy power of the dragon, continues... Enril is slowly succumbing to the influence of the Breath of Moon and believes that she is in love with Kyrette. Kyrette's plan to use and kill Enril to obtain the power of Nous seems to be moving according to plan. Except for the one thing he hadn't anticipated... The power of human emotion...
name: Vol. 8

description: Determined to drive an already trance-like Yulan to the edge, Enril refuses to give him elf's blood--the only thing that can save him--ensuring that the dragon's blood flowing through Yulan's veins will completely consume him. But if she succeeds, Yulan’s memory of all that he loves will be destroyed! Will Yulan allow himself to be taken over? Or will love prevail as the ultimate power?
name: Vol. 9

description:
In Volume 1, Ernan finds out from Rume that the Manas descendant is still alive. He gets tossed out from Rume’s cave with one hand completely mangled and the other healing with the help of his bodyguards. His bodyguards are introduced in this volume and they are extremely powerful and strong and helped Ernan become the commander of the knights.

Back Blurb

Raise An Army.

Rule The World.

Only One Can Be Archlord!

In this classic tale of a hero who must fulfill his destiny, a father takes his newborn son on a journey to be named. But when fortune and loyalty give way to betrayal and greed, it's up to an unlikely champion and one remarkable sword to restore honor and balance to the land!

Based on the Hit Video Game!

name: Vol. 1

description:
Back Blurb

Horrified that the descendant of Nathan Manas is still alive, Ernan sends out two of his best men to find and kill him. Meanwhile, Arin decides to journey with Zian and Ugdrasil to Elka to meet the great prophet Berouze. But when they meet two more travelers along the way in the Taas Forest, suspicions begin to mount on both sides...

Chapter Titles

  • Episode 8: Rume Traval's Trial, Part II
  • Episode 9: Argument and Departure

  • Episode 11: Interlopers
  • Episode 12: Camp Breaks

  • Episode 14: The Tass Melee, II
  • Episode 15: Ghosts of the Past
name: Vol. 2

description:
Back Blurb

Now embroiled in a clash with the four most powerful warriors in the land, John and his friends would be slaughtered if it weren't for the appearance of Father Kenneth. But even Kenneth's formidable force might not be enough. And when the tide changes, Arin, John and Ugdrasil get split up. Can they hazard their dangerous journey divided? Each will need help, and they may just get it from the mysterious denizens.

Chapter Titles

  • Episode 16: The Fall of Father Kenneth
  • Episode 17: Spit in the Devil's Eye
  • Episode 18: Nail's Betrayal

  • Episode 20: Lending A Hand

name: Vol. 3

description:
Back Blurb

As Zian struggles against the Captain of the Lizards -- rising as a hero -- the band of young warriors are hardly aware that a larger threat looms on the horizon. But when that threat unleashes the incredible power that Zian has had locked within him, Ugdrasil finds himself wondering if he should trust his lifelong -- but immature -- friend with it. And Zian isn't the only one who is the target of distrust. Ernan finds that his bid for power in the realm has many challengers...

Chapter Titles

  • Episode 25: To the Last Ounce of Strength
  • Episode 26: The Mage's Circle
  • Episode 27: Sacrifices
  • Episode 28: Revenge
  • Episode 29: Kralelion
  • Episode 30: Hidden Strength
  • Episode 31: Enemy Revealed
  • Episode 32: Disquiet
  • Episode 33: The King's Expedition
name: Vol. 4

description:
Back Blurb

An unlikely champion armed with a remarkable sword will restore honor and balance to the land!

In their search for the prophet Berouze, Arin and Ugdrasil arrive at Elka, a strange city where Elves, Gnomes, Kobalt and even Orcs freely roam the streets. Their search seems hopeless until they defend an old man from a band of thugs in knight's armor. What secrets of the city does this mysterious old man hold? Looks are more than deceiving in this volume of Archlord!

Chapter Titles

  • Episode 34: Long Awaited Arrivals
  • Episode 35: Legends Returned
  • Episode 36: Street Fighter
  • Episode 37: Street Fighter II
  • Episode 38: Gaiahon Revealed
  • Episode 39: Reunions
  • Episode 40: End of the Road
  • Episode 41: Cyripus
name: Vol. 5

description:
Back Blurb

Ewan wakes the great wizard Cyripus, only to be slain before he's even had a chance to fight. Cyripus then takes over Ernan's body in order to confront Gracia, who claims she summoned him back to life in order to destroy him once and for all. But when her arrows seem to have no effect, Cyripus reveals the vast breadth of his power: an army of humans planted with magical archon seeds that ill now come and serve him faithfully. But this battle isn't over until the swordsman sings and an unlikely hero reveals where her true strength lies...

Chapter Titles

  • Episode 42: Gracia Revealed
  • Episode 43: Reunion: The Bonds of Destiny Renewed
  • Episode 44: Awakenings
  • Episode 45: Sacrifice
  • Episode 46: Archord
name: Vol. 6

description: Beginning with the ravaging effects of Avengers Disassembled and following the aftermath of House of M, Civil War and Secret Invasion, culminating with the evil Reign of Norman Osborn, the Marvel Universe has been left with its greatest villains holding more power and control than ever before. On the brink of madness, Osborn, in his final bid to take total control, targets the final obstacle in his mission: Asgard. Events are set in motion forcing our heroes to put aside the deep rifts that have grown over the past seven years. Opposing them stand a horde of evil that has begun to take down the gods of the Golden Realm! SIEGE will rock the foundations of every super hero, villain and team in the Marvel Universe. As an era ends, one word will ring above all others: 'SIEGE.' Collecting SIEGE #1-4, SIEGE: THE CABAL and SIEGE digital prologue.

description: When a pounding Spider-Sense headache leads Spider-Man to the comatose body of his biggest, toughest foe, he realizes that something -- or someone -- can indeed stop the Juggernaut! But who? How? And who are they coming for next? Can Spider-Man find out before it's too late? And will Peter Parker ever get to have dinner with Carlie Cooper? Roger Stern and Lee Weeks return to unravel the mystery. Plus, relive a classic encounter between Spidey and Juggernaut from Amazing Spider-Man #229 & #230! Collecting AMAZING SPIDER-MAN #626-629 & #229-230

description: You're Bolivar Trask, the reanimated leader of the Mutant Response Division. Your mission: Kill every member of X-Factor. How to accomplish that without collateral damage? Easy: hire the team for what seems to be a routine case that will send them into a certain death trap. Problem solved. And in NATION X, Cyclops invites the world's only mutant detective agency to relocate to their floating island retreat and take up residence there. But will Madrox and his team believe that it's the best place for them? What old faces will pop up, and what old acquaintances will be renewed? And will there even be a Utopia left when the mysterious Crone shows up and threatens to bring the entire place crashing down into the Pacific? Collecting X-FACTOR #204-206 and NATION X: X-FACTOR.
name: Volume 10

description: Meet Daredevil as you've NEVER seen him before! The cataclysmic events of issue 500 left Matt in the toughest place of his life - and forced him to make the hardest decision he's ever made. Now's the start of a radically different chapter in Daredevil's adventures as the new creative team of Andy Diggle (THUNDERBOLTS) and Roberto De La Torre (IRON MAN) take DD to entirely new highs and lows! And in THE LIST, Norman Osborn's eye turns to Hell's Kitchen where he dispatches the only assassin he can rely on to kill Daredevil, Bullseye! But all is not as it seems. Collecting DAREDEVIL: DARK REIGN - THE LIST and DAREDEVIL #501-507.

description: Mutants are supposedly evolution's next step, but the High Evolutionary doesn't like where it's headed! All over the world, mutants are robbed of their powers, leaving X-Men and adversaries alike on the edge of defeat! But who is the Evolutionary's mysterious patron, and how is the disempowerment his next step? Plus: threats from the Acolytes, the Neo and more! Guest-starring the New Warriors, X-Force and more than thirty years' worth of robots! Collecting UNCANNY X-MEN #379-380, CABLE (1993) #78, X-FORCE (1991) #101, WOLVERINE (1988) #149 and X-MEN (1991) #99.
